EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 222300 UTC
AFTER THE BLOCKED CONDITIONS OF RECENT WEEKS A RETURN TO
THE MORE USUAL MOBILE PATTERN IS EXP FOR THIS PERIOD.
INITIALLY A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO EXTEND N-
EWARDS ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES DURING FRIDAY RELAXING
AWAY INTO THE CONTINENT BY SATURDAY NIGHT. THEREAFTER THE
DOMINANT FEATURE OF THE WEATHER WILL BE A LARGE LOW
PRESSURE SYSTEM WHICH WILL LIE TO THE N AND N-W OF THE
BRITISH ISLES FOR THE REST OF THE PERIOD. THIS SYSTEM MAY
WELL HAVE VARIOUS CENTRES ROTATING AROUND ONE ANOTHER
AND AROUND ITS SERN FLANK SMALLER INTENSE SYSTEMS COULD
RUN QCKY EWARDS OVER THE WEEKEND. WITH THE RIDGE CLEARING
NITON EARLY FRIDAY STRG WINDS WILL FEATURE FOR MUCH OF
THE FCST PERIOD WITH GALES POSS AT TIMES OVER THE
WEEKEND. INTO MONDAY THERE IS STILL MUCH UNCERTAINTY
HOWEVER IT IS POSS THAT A VIGOROUS LOW MAY DEVELOP WITHIN
NITON AREA. IN THIS CASE SEV GALE OR EVEN STORM FORCE
WINDS ARE POSS
